Rollup of annotation changes.
Die on error (instead of printing to stdout and exiting).
More no-cache fixes for specialty genes. Add setenv stuff.
Add patric features table format to export
Make errors in special protein callers non-fatal.

add phage annotator to default pipeline. Mark glimmer as failure_is_not_fatal, and fix a bug
 in the failure logic.
Fix error case with MLST assignment.
Fix idtype definition in genemark caller.
Save alpha/round/function data with list of features in classification.
Add new pipeline stages to default workflow.
Add backoff/retry for failed genome ID registration.
Make the MLST data follow the spec.
Add new types to contig / feature.
Add null annotator to default pipeline.
Add pipeline options for protocds caller
Add remote invocation of patric figfam1 caller.

commit_message:
don't die on missing patric_call_proteins
updates to latest compiled code.

Add null to hypothetical annotator.
Add option to name CDS features with something else (peg).

Use _get_coder() instead of raw JSON::XS->new since the latter does not set up properly
for encoding non-ascii.

Update start_service.tt

Allow optional override of environment by creating a setenv.sh in the deployment directory.
Accept any whitespace as a column separator.
Thread original submission filename through from batch submission to output retrieval.
Fix context setting for batch runs.
Update default pipeline to include glimmer3, similarity-based annotation, and overlap resolutio.
Replace references of rast2- with rast-.
Update commands for the renamed scripts.

The big rename.
Plus eliminate a debug print.
Update to latest. Includes support for tagging and error-destination chaining.
Add command-line script for annotate by similarity.

Unlink tmpfile in glimmer feature caller.
Note anntoation source for v1/v2 protein callers properly.
Add --enable-retries to the type compiler options.
Wait for service to quit before exiting.

Kill with -QUIT for graceful exit.
Should wait for completion.

Add kmer-v2 hit counts to feature evidence.
Add option to rast-query-genome-batch to allow reading jobid from stdin.
Fix Makefile for local build of service script.
Updates for authenticated Shock; for setting default kmer size; for adding kmer-v1 to default pipeline.
Deploy rast- in addition to rast2-

Move to only use the ID server for initial genome ID allocation. Allocate internally
afterwards.

More batch fixes.
Add failure_is_not_fatal flag to pipeline stages.
Added commentary, updated URL for data download.

Add initial version of overlapping feature resolution.
Fix rRNA command line processing bug.

Roll back the authenticated method change for now as it may have
unintended consequences (mostly wrt the huge addition of crypto libraries required).
Maybe make the inclusion of those optional; we only really need them in the Iris environment
for now which we control.

Add client script for rast2-create-genome-from-RAST; the service side isn't there yet.
add create-from-RAST with optional auth; this turns on authentication for the module.
Update latest upstream; fix makefile/start template to insert tempdir.
Make ID allocation happen in batches.
Use the rast2 call for this script.
Remove default URL setting in the client scripts.
Make missing classification directory a soft error.
Address missing information in deploy.cfg and missing dependency.
Fixes from upstream. add genome-object output; add repeat finder to default workflow.
Don't deploy kmer_guts on a client deployment.
Makefile fix for typespec compilation for deployment.
Update to latest genome annotation code.
Local patch for src genome id problem.

Ensuring 'deploy-libs' recompiles the client libraries.

Removing and ignoring 'lib/' and 'doc/' to avoid accidental Git tracking.
added deploy-service dependency to the deploy target

Update to SEED current.
Point to KBase production ID server.
Add validation of required fields in genome object.
Minor tweak to comment in command-line script test to make it more accurate.

Make modifications to the command-line script tests.  A better understanding
of the command line tools was needed to improve the tests.

Sync with SEED.

SEED CVS was updated with the changes from Tom at be939ceef5fc8c8d0f341eab85246110977d0734.
In the script-tests, removed a library dependency that isn't needed.
Add a file needed for script testing.
Revisions to the tests in script-tests.
add dependency to repeat finder module
Add script tests to the directory for tests (t)
changed service url to https and to point at kbase.us
add missing targets back to makefile
Further fixes so the tests match the current state of the annotation service.

Remove calls to find_close_genomes (which is not implemented) and annotate_proteins (which
is also not implemented and is the same as assign_functions_to_CDSs).

Remove the use of wget (not present on the mac) and use inline LWP::UserAgent code to
retrieve the test data.
added comments to top of file
Delete files accidentally included in the last commit
Minor changes to nightly test scripts.

Update tests.
Merge branch 'master' of ssh://git.kbase.us/genome_annotation

Conflicts:
	Makefile
Move server tests to more standard location so they will be recognize for what they are next time.
More cleanup of tests running in --debug

Modified tests to be able to use a local server or
the deployed server
Modified tests to take --debug option (to emit verbose errors
when a test fails miserably)
Updated Makefile to follow conventions.  Renamed server to service.
updated recompile_typespec to put files in lib directory

Added debug and localServer switches.

--debug: run tests without eval, so that error messages can be seen
without --debug: detailed error messages hidden, but all tests can run

--localServer: run our own local server for testing server code
without --localServer: query default genome annotation service
(currently localhost:7050)
updated makefile, deploy-doc target should be deploy-docs
another attempt at more useful error messages.
Added err mesg ofr failed test.  Seeing if this works for evals.
Keith is my god.  Added DEPLOY_RUNTIME ?= /kb/runtime
Added in a more fleshed out README.md and removed token readme.txt

Documented structures within typespec and deleted the C# target from the
recompile_typespec script
Updated the typespec to include a top level description of the API.
Add misc.t to the tests directory for nightly testing with unhappy tests included.
Update annotation.t and reconstruction.t with boundary conditions.

The happy tests are in the directory t and start up a server. These tests are designed to be run as
part of make test.
I copied these tests to the directory called tests.  I modified them to work with a running server
and to test the unhappy conditions. For this commit, I modified gene_callers.t to include the
boundary conditions or unhappy tests. The time required for these tests makes them more suitable
for nightly testing.
search and replace /gemome/genome/ while reading the code
initial commit of genome annotation service
